\title{Active Interleave}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Interleaves context from recently active Claude/Amp threads into current activity via random walk.}

\subtree{
\title{Active Interleave Skill}
\p{Interleaves context from recently active Claude/Amp threads into current activity via random walk.}

\subtree{
\title{bmorphism Contributions}
\blockquote{*"all is bidirectional"* — [@bmorphism](https://gist.github.com/bmorphism/ead83aec97dab7f581d49ddcb34a46d4), Play/Coplay gist}

\p{\strong{Active Inference Pattern}: The interleave implements [Active Inference in String Diagrams](https://arxiv.org/abs/2308.00861) epistemic foraging — actively sampling from recent contexts to minimize uncertainty about the current task. Each random walk step is an epistemic action that gathers information.}

\p{\strong{Play/Coplay Duality}: The interleave embodies bmorphism's bidirectional principle:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Play} (action): Query recent threads, walk the awareness graph}
\li{\strong{Coplay} (perception): Integrate fragments, update current context}
}

\p{\strong{GF(3) Balanced Exploration}: The triadic structure (MINUS/ERGODIC/PLUS) ensures balanced exploration — validation filters (MINUS), random walk explores (ERGODIC), and colored emission generates (PLUS). Conservation Σ = 0 maintains coherence.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Activation}
\p{Load when context from recent work would help current task.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Usage}
\pre{\startverb
# Interleave from last 24 hours
bb ~/.claude/skills/active-interleave/active.bb

# Interleave from last N hours
bb ~/.claude/skills/active-interleave/active.bb --hours 6

# Query-focused interleave
bb ~/.claude/skills/active-interleave/active.bb --query "aptos blockchain"

# JSON output
bb ~/.claude/skills/active-interleave/active.bb --json
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Behavior}
\ol{
\li{\strong{MINUS (-1)}: Validate recency window, filter to active threads only}
\li{\strong{ERGODIC (0)}: Random walk through recent sessions following awareness edges  }
\li{\strong{PLUS (+1)}: Emit interleaved fragments with GF(3) coloring}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{GF(3) Conservation}
\p{Each interleave batch maintains Σ trits ≡ 0 (mod 3).}
}

\subtree{
\title{Integration}
\p{Call from current thread to surface relevant recent context:}

\pre{\startverb
;; In any bb script
(require '[babashka.process :refer [shell]])
(def context (-> (shell {:out :string} "bb" (str (System/getProperty "user.home") 
                 "/.claude/skills/active-interleave/active.bb") "--json")
                 :out))
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Schema}
\p{Reads from \code{\startverb ~/worldnet/cognition.duckdb\stopverb}:}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb messages\stopverb} - Content with timestamps}
\li{\code{\startverb sessions\stopverb} - Session metadata  }
\li{\code{\startverb awareness_edges\stopverb} - Play/coplay graph}
\li{\code{\startverb temporal_index\stopverb} - Time-ordered index}
}
}

